1
00:00:00,416 --> 00:00:03,666
They offered to cancel half of my sentence

2
00:00:03,916 --> 00:00:06,291
In exchange for me handing over my
brother who had not been detained

3
00:00:06,708 --> 00:00:09,791
He would come in, and I would be released instead

4
00:00:10,125 --> 00:00:13,208
I claimed that our relationship was normal

5
00:00:13,416 --> 00:00:15,500
And I did not expect him to come for me

6
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:16,958
If he was outside the area

7
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,541
And that it was their mistake

8
00:00:18,666 --> 00:00:21,750
Because they had already detained
him earlier on multiple charges

9
00:00:22,041 --> 00:00:25,666
And still could not get anything from him

10
00:00:25,916 --> 00:00:28,083
So I was not obliged to do that

11
00:00:29,625 --> 00:00:32,041
When I was released, they tried to bargain with me to join them

12
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:35,208
At the same time a Syrian regime convoy arrived

13
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:37,166
Along with the Russians

14
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:39,125
On their way to Tabqa city

15
00:00:39,875 --> 00:00:43,708
They tried to convince me to take a weapon from them

16
00:00:43,875 --> 00:00:47,416
And fight alongside them if we shared the same cause

17
00:00:47,583 --> 00:00:49,833
As proof of my loyalty to them

18
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:55,291
Interviewer: And how did they react to your refusal?

19
00:00:55,708 --> 00:00:57,375
Of course, I refused in an indirect way

20
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:59,791
By saying that I was the youngest in my family

21
00:00:59,875 --> 00:01:03,833
And that my mother would never abandon me after prison

22
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:05,875
And I had no idea how her health was

23
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,708
So how could I get out and take up arms immediately
